[It is clear that One Health, WHO, and OIE need to run an anthrax continuing education workshop in India to bring their medical services up to date on this disease and to better improve medical-veterinary interaction.

For years Andhra Pradesh was reporting bovine outbreaks in double digits, but in 2009 it was only 9 outbreaks and in 2012 and 2013 it was single outbreaks. But it is still a problem with sheep and goats, with significant within herd and flock losses.

For a map of India showing Andhra Pradesh, go to: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_physio-2001.jpg. Anthrax is an especially troubling problem along India's SE coastline states.

Our thanks to Sabine for forwarding this report. - Mod.MHJ

